reaction is a header-only library that provides CMake targets:

  find_package(reaction CONFIG REQUIRED)
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE reaction::reaction)

Example usage:

  #include <reaction.h>

  // Create reactive variables
  auto a = reaction::var(1);
  auto b = reaction::var(2);

  // Create computed values
  auto sum = reaction::calc([]() { return a() + b(); });

  // Values automatically update when dependencies change
  a.value(10); // sum will automatically update to 12


